In a large skillet, cook beef, onion and garlic over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain. Stir in the hominy, chili, tomato sauce, water, chili powder, salt and pepper. Transfer to a greased 13-in. x 9-in. x 2-in. baking dish. Sprinkle with corn chips. Bake, uncovered, at 350 degrees F for 30 minutes or until heated through.